channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Rogue Agency: GOP Lawmakers Scrutinize the Consumer Financial Protection Bureau
Schumer pushes for bump stock ban after SCOTUS reverses Trump-era rule
item.description: Schumer revealed his plan to bring a bill to ban bump stocks to the Senate for a potential vote this week, noting that he will need Republican assistance.

item.title: Kari Lake to Newsmax: Biden 'Rolled Out the Welcome Mat' at Border
item.description: Kari Lake, a candidate in the Republican Senate primary in Arizona, told Newsmax on Monday that President Joe Biden and others in the Democrat Party have "rolled out the welcome mat" with their border policies.

item.title: Biden Made Another Bizarre Remark at LA Fundraiser That Has Everyone Talking
John Kerry used government email alias as secretary of state, whistleblowers say
item.description: Former Secretary of State John Kerry used a pseudonymous government email address while serving as the nation’s top diplomat during the Obama administration, whistleblowers alleged.

item.title: Sherman: Trump Stands by American Farmers, So Should We
item.description: Our farmers work long hours and hard days to feed America. They’re the bedrock of our society. After all, what kind of secure nation cannot feed itself? Do we want to be dependent on countries like China for our food?

item.title: Dr. Fauci and the Beagles: 2.5 years Later Redstate Is Vindicated As WaPo Backtracks on His Defense
Ex-CIA deputy director sounds the alarm about terror threat posed by open border
item.description: Former CIA Deputy Director Mike Morrell warned the Biden administration may need to use emergency authorities to keep terrorists from crossing the border.

item.title: Trump Seeking 'Fighter' as Running Mate
item.description: Presumptive Republican presidential nominee Donald Trump is seeking a "Goldilocks" candidate and "fighter" as his vice president pick, the Guardian reported Monday, citing sources connected to the former president.

item.title: 'Unthinkable': Patricia Heaton Says What Needed to Be Said About the Cruelty of Jill Biden
'Greatest threat': Former top Kamala Harris aide reveals which Trump VP pick could sink her candidacy
item.description: A former communications director for Vice President Harris said GOP Sen. JD Vance is “super smart" and poses the "greatest threat" to her vice presidency in 2024.

item.title: Larry Hogan Highlights Independence in New Ad
item.description: Maryland Republican Senate candidate Larry Hogan launched a new advertisement Monday that underscores his political independence.

item.title: Karine Jean-Pierre Responds to Videos of Biden Being Senile, and Her Explanation Is Astonishing
Trump pulls away from Biden in one-time swing state: poll
item.description: Former President Donald Trump holds an 18-point lead over President Biden in Iowa, according to a new poll in a one-time crucial general election battleground state that Barack Obama won twice

item.title: White House Accused of Derailing Support for Ethics Bill
item.description: Rep. Katie Porter, D-Calif., accused the White House of derailing Democrat support for a bipartisan executive ethics bill on which she and House Oversight Committee Chair James Comer, R-Ky., joined forces.
